Overview

Little River Park is located on the shores of Pine Creek Lake. It boasts beautiful views of the water along with many recreational opportunities. The swimming beach and hiking trail are popular places within the site, and the lake is great for canoeing and fishing.

Natural Features:

Pine Creek Lake lies in the southeast corner of Oklahoma, at the edge of the Ouachita Mountains. The lake spans 3,750 acres with 74 miles of shoreline. Prairie lands and lush hardwood forests surround the lake.

Recreation:

Popular activities include swimming, fishing, picnicking, hiking and boating. A hiking trail is accessible from the campground.

Facilities:

Little River Park offers numerous campsites, many of which have electric and water hookups. The group camping shelter comes with five electric hookups. Additional amenities include showers, a dump station, playground and boat ramp.

Nearby Attractions:

The north end of the lake extends to Pine Creek State Park. Here, hikers can explore the Love Run and Spike Buck Trails. The historic ruins of nearby Fort Towson are interesting as well.
properties.FacilityDirections: From Broken Bow, OK, take Highway 3 south 23 miles to the park entrance. Turn south at the sign and follow the access road.
